g**\\n\\nI’m thinking I need to make all top-level test classes public since the existing class isn’t. I might consider using nested static classes, and maybe the constructor can be private. I’ll have to test setAccessible and getDeclared methods, but private reflection may need allowWrite. Class#newInstance requires a public no-arg constructor, so I wonder if using StringBuilder is safe and if it's registered automatically in a native image. Would it be better to use a public nested class?\\n\\n**Evaluating Constructor Behavior**\\n\\nI’m trying to understand a situation where I want to convert something, but it doesn’t seem relevant anymore. I noticed that using `newInstanceIfPossible(ConstructorOnlyPojo.class)` with the constructor taking String and Integer gives null values, which is puzzling. Although the ConstructorOnly constructor is capable of handling null values, it leads me to wonder about the behavior with primitives — are the defaults different when they're involved? It feels like there’s complexity here that I need to unravel!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0b06730402872aed0169f615ddaf58819e8046a27550347eb0\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9hX4KGtUZLkgTAoMObWm-5l8zYlSrBxA-5JBySE7ffWfUlsobpN7nwhpXJkD0smSTcCvFt1GrvOJXdp0C2yfoY1jsJORbHt_aU-8dJfwg3EJN-RFmUN4JCkiQ3uzsiHyGyI6wWSO8Dc-IDIcSh7--f0YK6kw1mQirm8obn4t4Th9qHvsf9E2TjYzX_LwaCX3okvndNiBM86vUA9Ljsv7RocpOTpkhTXXm-WkEko1gYRts4QkowvPQ16b7y2bkAqxVmLex36M4NYrSLzmp3qcdWp59bu7piIoT-ArDMNCHLorFMd_UfhPs1uQzYuM8Owhe87ZWCUNu-UtQFl7hkPHUhITzHmmutvzEyutklBdtj-fS02TmhfBwQdgaxML2XBFCj11Woo6ftF_-SKel-65sOaLW5CT_KlR6_ydC-MDRIV5gw-aEJtVo09HY7uqp1gdt6cf0uHBCTIDd9O3NBZ2XQEkuUshxyNEDj1AYVyQLs8dpbohdw8j1pg6xWEJ_t-3rj1mN4h3yiJcKaOg8xQgRe3XmQr8D3LwIfcsOfVjI1LAyjygtchFcl1tE5s59_Dk69fDtn7-dJZyw4DwUHPRhQZA5O8hxnSuPvE0RSqXNeCIe9MS7Qw006J3408VP3_P32BuJISXxbiv-Ba_Zn6BV6auhhQE2Aau8bOCc2a1lAi8jV5NAy_lFW51otw6l5QQuM0ti85NWaL4KeI3aDwRlT8iqAB8xXaTzdQ02sxgNLSzbbIcv4xjpWJSPVX0DC8VgfBX